The specter of a trade war is the biggest risk for the euro area as the European Central BankÂ prepares to end asset purchases, a Bloomberg survey of economists showed. Policy makers are warning against the detrimental effects protectionist policies can have on confidence, arguing at the same time that domestic momentum remains strong. The Governing Council will meet July 26 to discuss monetary policy and is expected to repeat its pledge that interest rates will remain at record lows at least through the summer of 2019.